# System Snapshot Is Authoritative

**SYSTEM_SNAPSHOT.md** at the project root is the authoritative reference for the current stack state.

When you make (or are asked to make) any **structural** change to the app, you **must** update SYSTEM_SNAPSHOT.md in the same work. Structural changes include:

- Adding, removing, or renaming **front-end routes** (app/ pages, layouts, error boundaries)
- Adding, removing, or renaming **API routes** (app/api/**/route.ts)
- Adding, removing, or changing **environment variables** (including usage locations)
- Changing **Vercel configuration** (vercel.json, deployment behavior)
- Changing **build pipeline** (package.json scripts, next.config.*, tsconfig, eslint/postcss)
- Adding or changing **integration points** (external services, internal call flows, storage, rate limits)
- Adding or removing **components** or **lib** modules that are part of the documented architecture

After editing the snapshot, add or update a **Verification log** entry (section “Verification Log – YYYY‑MM‑DD”) with the date and a brief note on what was verified or changed.
